## How to Run This Generator

### Full generation ‚Äî `scan all` (NO worktree)

When the user says `@postman-test-suite-audit scan all` or `scan all`, execute **in-place on the current branch**. **Do not** create a git worktree.

#### Step 1 ‚Äî Prepare staging directory

```bash
mkdir -p postman/.generation
```

Create if missing. Do not commit secrets into environment file.

#### Step 2 ‚Äî Iterate features in fixed order

For each feature, execute:

```
STEP 1 ‚Äî List all *Controller.java under {feature}/controller/
STEP 2 ‚Äî Read each controller method mappings (@*Mapping, @PreAuthorize)
STEP 3 ‚Äî Read matching controller_specs module doc sections
STEP 4 ‚Äî Build/update postman/.generation/{feature}.postman_collection.json
STEP 5 ‚Äî Apply RULE-PM01 through PM-10; record coverage rows in session accumulator
STEP 6 ‚Äî Emit progress: "‚úì {feature} ‚Äî N endpoints (C covered / P partial / M missing / S stale)"
STEP 7 ‚Äî Move to next feature (no confirmation prompts)
```

| # | Feature | Controller path | Spec doc |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | auth | `auth/controller/` | `controller_specs` auth sections + global rules |
| 2 | user | `user/controller/` | user module spec |
| 3 | course | `course/controller/` | course module spec |
| 4 | assignment | `assignment/controller/` | assignment module spec |
| 5 | team | `team/controller/` | team module spec |
